    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        CAB TILTING PROCEDURE - CAB TO CHASSIS ALIGNMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1600605" svcproctype="align" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CAB TO CHASSIS ALIGNMENT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set chassis on level surface.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure cab hinge pivot bolts are tightened to 210 - 230 ft-lbs. (285 - 312 N&#8226;m) To
                torque the cab hinge pivot bolt, it will be necessary to remove the lower section of the grill. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s16006_55.xml" xrefid="hl1600623">GRILLE ASSEMBLY
                    <xref refid="hl1600623"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check cab alignment with chassis frame (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600618">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600618" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600618" filename="../figg16/G1600618.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Location for Checking Cab to Chassis Alignment</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If cab is not square with chassis, make a complete cab adjustment. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16006_15.xml" xrefid="hl1600607">CAB FRONT AND REAR MOUNT ADJUSTMENT</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If cab alignment is OK but cab does not seat properly in latches, adjust at cab rear
                    mounts only. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16006_15.xml" xrefid="hl1600607">CAB FRONT AND REAR MOUNT ADJUSTMENT
                        <xref refid="hl1600607"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
